-1245782303.text: "Our results has uncovered a previously unrealized role of GSK3beta Y216 phosphorylation : it triggers GSK3beta recruitment of beta-TrCP and subsequent GSK3beta monoubiquitination by beta-TrCP, an event required for Wnt induced inhibition of beta-catenin degradation, thus identifying phosphorylation of GSK3beta Y216 as an ' activator ' of the Wnt and beta-catenin pathway."
